# pr-view-valid.json.meta — provenance sidecar (#347 W1c2, #398).
#
# Canonical `gh pr view --json <fields>` payload shape carrying the full W1c1
# vocabulary — the runner drives `chp_pr_view` with various FIELDS_CSV subsets
# to prove:
#
#   - normalized-shape projection: EXACTLY the requested fields appear in
#     stdout; unrequested vocabulary fields are ABSENT (not silently promoted).
#   - `comments` normalizes to `[{id,author,body,createdAt}]` ascending by
#     createdAt (fixture is intentionally OUT-OF-ORDER to prove the leaf sorts).
#   - `reviews` normalizes to `[{author,state,submittedAt}]` ascending by
#     submittedAt (fixture out-of-order likewise).
#   - `closingIssueNumbers` folds the raw `closingIssuesReferences` collection
#     to an int array (the GitHub-internal shape does NOT cross the seam). The
#     fixture uses the FLAT `[{number}]` array shape real `gh pr view --json
#     closingIssuesReferences` returns (the pre-existing repo-wide idiom, see
#     `lib-pr-linkage.sh:85` which selects `.closingIssuesReferences[]?`); the
#     leaf's `(A.nodes // A // [])` fold also accepts the GraphQL cursor
#     `{nodes:[…]}` shape some queries emit, so both are supported. The unit
#     parity suite (test-w1c2-incidental-read-parity.sh) exercises the cursor
#     shape too.
#   - `body: null` normalizes to `""` per the vocabulary.
#   - Fail-CLOSED: gh-stub failure → verb rc≠0 with no partial stdout.
#   - `author` (issue #495, pr_view-only 15th member): flattens the raw
#     `{login:"eve"}` object to the bare string `"eve"` (the pre-existing
#     comment/review author-flattening idiom). Rejected (rc 2) on
#     `chp_pr_list` / `chp_find_pr_for_issue` — see `_run_findpr_assert` /
#     `_run_prlist_assert` in the runner.
